description.narrative: Output 2.4 Education system is capable to provide quality and inclusive learning and development to the most disadvantaged children and adolescents., which contributes to Access To Quality Learning Opportunities, Access To Quality Learning Opportunities (Covid), Cross Sectoral - Gender Discriminatory Roles And Practices, Equitable Access To Quality Education, Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement, Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement (Covid), Safe And Equitable Water, Sanitation And Hygiene Services And Practices, Water, Sanitation And Hygiene Systems And Empowerment Of Communities, Water, Sanitation And Hygiene Systems And Empowerment Of Communities (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022, disadvantaged children have equitable access to health and education services to survive, learn, develop and contribute to resilient, inclusive and sustainable communities

title.narrative: Output 2.4 Education system is capable to provide quality and inclusive learning and development to the most disadvantagedchildren and adolescents.

description.narrative: By applying innovative solutions to provide high-quality and inclusive learning and development to the most disadvantaged boys and girls, UNICEF supported the implementation of digital learning platform projects, launched applications for teachers, parents and caregivers, provided courses on gender-sensitive teaching and application of the Gender Action Learning System (GALS) methodology, and supported reintegration of repatriated children from Iraq by developing their individual learning plans and providing support to parents, teachers and school administrators. Ongoing system-strengthening work on EMIS contributed to innovative data collection and work towards an interoperable data management system aligned with other key datasets on children. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:24/01/2022
